    <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText><![CDATA[<pre>By Mr. McKINLEY:H.R. 4937.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:According to Article I, Section 8, Clause 3 of theConstitution: The Congress shall have power to enact thislegislation to regulate commerce with foreign nations, andamong the several states, and with the Indian tribes.[Page H5640]</pre>]]></constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
